# ========================================
BUG REPORT

SUMMARY
AMS R1 2026 - Undo Delete of Parcel is Not Working on AMS Respond to Findings Screen

COMPONENT
AMS - Respond to Findings - Delete / Recover Parcel

ENVIRONMENT
CENTEST

ROUND
Round 1 - 2026

SEVERITY
High

PRIORITY
High

LABELS
AMS, RespondToFindings, DeleteParcel, UndoDelete, Round1, Bug

# ========================================
DESCRIPTION

When a user (Advisor/Agent or Farmer) has marked a parcel for deletion on the AMS Respond to Findings screen, the Undo/Recover option to reverse that deletion is not working as expected. After a parcel has been successfully marked for deletion (strikethrough visible, yellow warning banner present, green toast confirmed), the user attempts to recover the parcel by selecting the Recover option on the deleted parcel row. The undo/recover action fails - the parcel is not restored to its original state. This is a regression against last year’s functionality where undo delete worked correctly.

# ========================================
STEPS TO REPRODUCE

Step 1
Log in to BISS on CENTEST as an Agent or Farmer with an AMS Round 1 profile
Use SQL: select * from VWBS_AMS_NOTIFIED_HERD where scheme_year = 2026 and expired = 0 and rownum <= 5 order by herd_no
Get agent login from BISS_INET: SELECT hbcus.bcus_bus_id AS HERDNO, MIN(ui.uri_username) AS USERNAME FROM tdco_customer_asscs ca, tdco_business_customers abcus, tdco_business_customers hbcus, tdcr_user_info ui WHERE SYSDATE BETWEEN ca.ca_start_date AND ca.ca_end_date AND ca.ca_cac_code = 194 AND ca.ca_bcus_id_from = abcus.bcus_id AND ca.ca_bcus_id_to = hbcus.bcus_id AND ui.uri_ccs_bus_id = abcus.bcus_bus_id AND hbcus.bcus_bus_id = ‘<HERD_NUMBER>’ GROUP BY hbcus.bcus_bus_id HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT ui.uri_username) = 1

Step 2
If Agent: Navigate to Agent Tools and select AMS then select the client herd to go to Farmer Dashboard
If Farmer: Navigate to Farmer Dashboard directly

Step 3
Click Respond to Findings button on the AMS Findings panel

Step 4
Locate a Red parcel in the findings list and click on it to open the side drawer

Step 5
Click the bin/delete symbol in the side drawer

Step 6
Confirm the deletion in the popup - verify the message reads:
“You have requested to delete this parcel from your BISS application. This may affect payment on other Area based schemes. Please undo if this was done in error”

Step 7
Click Save Changes
Verify green toast: You have successfully marked parcel X for deletion
Verify strikethrough on the parcel row
Verify yellow warning banner: You have decided to delete a parcel. This may affect your payments

Step 8
Locate the parcel row that has a strikethrough indicating it is marked for deletion

Step 9
Click the Recover option on the deleted parcel row

Step 10
Click Save Changes

Step 11
Observe the parcel row and the AMS response screen

# ========================================
ACTUAL RESULT

The Undo/Recover action does not work correctly. The parcel is not restored to its original state after clicking Recover and saving. The strikethrough remains on the parcel row and/or the yellow warning banner persists and/or the parcel values do not revert to their original state.

# ========================================
EXPECTED RESULT

After clicking Recover on the deleted parcel row and saving changes the following should occur:

1. The yellow warning banner “You have decided to delete a parcel. This may affect your payments” should be removed from the top of the AMS response screen
1. The strikethrough should be removed from the parcel row
1. The parcel should revert to its original values with no response selected
1. The side drawer should reflect the original parcel state - no deletion applied
1. This behaviour was working correctly in the previous year - this is a regression

